                  <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  <msItem>
                     <p>
                        <placeName key="place_108012">Daventry</placeName> and <placeName>Drayton</placeName>, The Symond Holding.

Indenture by which <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> son of <persName>
                              <forename>Robert</forename> 
                              <surname>Symond</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                              </placeName>
                           </persName>
                        </persName> gives to <persName nymRef="Neel">
                           <forename>Margery</forename> late the wife</persName> of <persName>
                           <forename>Robert</forename> 
                           <surname>Neel</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                           </placeName>
                        </persName> 1½ acres 1 rood situated thus:—½ ac. in the southern field above the <placeName type="minor">Lok</placeName> by the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Simon</forename> 
                           <surname>Newbolde</surname>
                        </persName>: ½ ac. in the western field under the <placeName type="minor">Lyche</placeName> by the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Thomas</forename> 
                           <surname>Spicer</surname>
                        </persName>: ½ acre in the northern field over <placeName type="minor">Langden</placeName> by the land of <persName>
                           <forename>Walter</forename> le <surname>Meleward</surname>
                        </persName>: and a rood in <placeName type="minor">Radmondeslond</placeName> by the land of <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> le  <surname>Werrour</surname>
                        </persName>. 
   Witnesses: <persName>
                           <forename>Geoffrey</forename> le <surname>porter</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_108013">Drayton</placeName>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Goodchere</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Baudewyne</surname>
                        </persName>,
   <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Baudewine</surname>
                        </persName>, 
   <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Adam</surname>
                        </persName>. 
   Given at <placeName role="person" key="place_108012">D<supplied>aventry</supplied>
                        </placeName>. 
   <origDate when="1349-07-02">
                           <supplied>2 July 1349.</supplied>
                        </origDate>
                     </p>
